      },
      "date": "2017-08-14 16:14:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Its the evolution of the locking that happened over time. The only reason this is here is for RHEL6 which has no locking of any kind. In later kernels that lockings is done in the core kernel code. At first its done with __kernel_param_[un]lock() but in the latest kernels that moved to kernel_param_[un]lock(). In that move __kernel_param_[un]lock() was no longer exported.\n\nOK.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
